Hi Dave,

I just installed 1.6.0 from the .msi under WinXP.  I use Cantera in
Matlab (version 7, Release 14).  It appears that the 'display.m' file
was omitted from the ...\cantera\@Solution directory.  Currently, when
a Gas Object is called in Matlab, I only see the:

G = 

	Solution object: 1-by-1

message.  I added the old (v1.5.4, I think) 'display.m' file to the
appropriate folder, and the old "solution display" functionality is
restored.

I see that in your new Tutorial file, the display functionality is
updated with enthalpy, entropy, etc. values.  It would be great to
have this in the new v1.6.0, but in the meantime, I figured I'd let
you know that this file is missing so that you can add either the old
one, or hopefully the new one to the .msi installer.  Also, it appears
that the 'clear.m' file is missing from that folder as well, although
I don't know how critical it is to use Cantera's clear as opposed to
Matlab's internal clear function.

I'm going to continue to play around with 1.6.0, and I'll let you know
if I come across anything else.

Thanks,
-A.J.
